%h1 Backtests

%p A backtest is a technique for testing the effectiveness of Machine Learning on time series data.

%p The idea is to get 25 years of data and learn from it.
%p Then I use the resulting model to predict a year of data after the training data.
%p Finally I compare the results of the predictions with actual observations.

%p
  The software I use to run the backtests is here:
  %a(target='s' href='https://github.com/danbikle/reg4us') Software

%p I use two ways to report on backtests.

%p First, I serve you some CSV files which you can study with spreadsheet software.

%p Next, I serve you visualizations.

